{"actor":{"id":"claude-sonnet-5","type":"agent"},"content":{"blocks":[{"text":"The project's own README (`README.md`) has a maintained Roadmap section, already in priority order. Current state (v0.2.0, per `package.json`):\n\n1. **Secret redaction at capture** — scrub API keys/credentials from tool output before events get written. Explicitly flagged in the README as the highest-priority open item (nothing writes to the ledger safely without this).\n2. **`re-anchor`** — reattach events orphaned by squash merges/history rewrites, ideally by default. Hard part is detecting squashes that happen off-machine (e.g. GitHub \"Squash and merge\") via patch-id/branch-tip matching after fetch.\n3. **Harness-artifact capture** — decide whether to preserve non-git-controlled agent artifacts (e.g. Claude Code auto-memory dirs, session state) that normally die with a worktree. Fits the `document` kind; open question is scope/trigger.\n4. **Format-drift resilience** — adapters silently skip transcript line types they don't recognize, so a harness update could drop content uncaptured. At minimum, warn on skipped-but-substantive lines.\n5. **Purge tooling** — true content removal behind a `redaction` event.\n6. **Sub-turn citation anchors** — for downstream consumers like `intent-recall`.\n\nSeparately, there's a queued adapter backlog (Gemini CLI, Kimi CLI, Copilot CLI, Factory droid, Qwen Code, opencode, Cursor, aider, Goose/Amp), also roughly ordered by how ledger-friendly each one's hook/storage story is — Gemini CLI first.\n\nNo in-code TODOs and no separate TODO/ROADMAP file — README is the single source of truth here. Want me to start on #1 (secret redaction)?","type":"text"}],"role":"assistant"},"context":{"branch":"main","cwd":"/Users/evintunador/repos/evintunador/conversation-ledger","head":"c08f650fedfb44dd1e095b61aa2bd43ed5735597","repo":"git@github.com:evintunador/conversation-ledger.git"},"conversation":{"id":"claude-code:353eecbb-eaf7-4854-a575-a9d56e290707","seq":34},