{"actor":{"type":"human"},"content":{"blocks":[{"content":"1\t# Product intent\n2\t\n3\t## Purpose\n4\t\n5\tConversation Ledger preserves durable, inspectable records of visible\n6\tconversations between people and coding agents. It is a general conversation\n7\tprovenance primitive, not an intent-analysis product. Downstream consumers may\n8\tuse its records as evidence about why a repository changed, but the ledger must\n9\tnot impose that interpretation.\n10\t\n11\tThe record must remain useful to consumers beyond a single tool: cross-CLI\n12\tcontinuity, archival/export, code attribution, review, and later intent\n13\tretrieval are all valid independent uses.\n14\t\n15\t## Behavioral commitments\n16\t\n17\t- Preserve source material and provenance; do not silently rewrite history.\n18\t- Preserve exact visible turns before creating optional derived views.\n19\t- Retain enough provenance for consumers to determine applicability without\n20\t  treating any record as timeless truth.\n21\t- Record the repository, branch, commit, worktree state, author, timestamps,\n22\t  and capture mechanism with each artifact whenever available.\n23\t- Keep storage out of ordinary working-tree status views while retaining normal\n24\t  Git durability and shareability.\n25\t- Make sharing, retention, redaction, and deletion deliberate user choices.\n26\t\n27\t## Non-goals for the foundation\n28\t\n29\t- Deciding which historical statement is correct or intended.\n30\t- Summarizing, ranking, embedding, or otherwise interpreting conversations.\n31\t- Controlling an agent, enforcing a workflow, or orchestrating agents.\n32\t- Capturing reasoning the provider hides (visible reasoning is recorded when\n33\t  exposed), or claiming it can reproduce a native agent session.\n34\t\n35\tThose belong to clients such as Turnbridge and Intent Recall, not to this core\n36\tstorage layer.\n37\t","tool_use_id":"toolu_014GF2osJ2GikSEN9aDKPnX3","type":"tool_result"}],"role":"user"},"context":{"branch